WEBVTT

00:00.929 --> 00:02.961
Previously on Roswell, New Mexico...

00:02.985 --> 00:04.507
Max's heart is never beating again.

00:04.532 --> 00:06.851
He died of a massive heart attack.
The organ is shredded.

00:06.876 --> 00:08.709
KYLE: Liz thinks we could
do a heart transplant.

00:08.734 --> 00:10.382
ALEX: She wants to use Noah's heart?

00:10.407 --> 00:12.516
MICHAEL: The pod keeps us
in stasis by regenerating

00:12.541 --> 00:14.466
our cells at the same rate they degrade.

00:14.491 --> 00:16.750
This current will speed
up the regeneration

00:16.775 --> 00:18.789
so Max will actually improve in there.

00:18.814 --> 00:21.390
(ELECTRICITY SPARKING)

00:30.365 --> 00:31.878
YOUNG MAX: He's out here.

00:31.933 --> 00:33.011
Don't you feel it?

00:33.036 --> 00:35.581
I feel like you owe me both
those grape sodas you brought.

00:35.606 --> 00:37.124
There he is.

00:39.554 --> 00:40.929
Leave me alone.

00:40.954 --> 00:42.791
- Get out of here.
- Y-You don't remember us?

00:42.816 --> 00:44.652
I remember you. I don't know you.

00:44.677 --> 00:46.988
I-I've been looking for you.
We didn't know your name.

00:47.066 --> 00:49.628
Michael Guerin. After nobody
adopted me for a year,

00:49.653 --> 00:52.079
they just stuck me with the name
of that trucker who found us.

00:52.104 --> 00:53.199
But all you got to know about me

00:53.231 --> 00:54.574
is I want to be left the hell alone!

00:54.599 --> 00:55.879
That's why I'm all the way out here,

00:55.904 --> 00:57.746
because I want to be alone!

00:57.771 --> 01:00.308
Okay. W-We'll leave you alone, okay?

01:00.590 --> 01:01.758
If that's what you want.

01:01.872 --> 01:03.814
(EXHALES)

01:05.634 --> 01:07.319
But if you change your mind,

01:07.344 --> 01:09.035
there's this diner, the Crashdown.

01:09.060 --> 01:10.821
I'll be there every day.

01:10.846 --> 01:12.222
Okay?

01:12.307 --> 01:14.825
In case you want a burger or something.

01:23.372 --> 01:24.498
Hey!

01:24.523 --> 01:25.793
I didn't ask for that!

01:25.818 --> 01:27.838
I didn't ask you for anything!

01:35.873 --> 01:37.353
The hell is this?

01:37.378 --> 01:40.423
When I'm finished, it's going
to be a rebuilt classic.

01:41.664 --> 01:43.079
Relax, Sanders.

01:43.104 --> 01:45.523
I'm just fixing it up for a
buddy who's on his way home.

01:45.844 --> 01:48.484
You're meant to be working
on Riley's tractor.

01:48.601 --> 01:50.695
Riley picked up the
tractor this morning.

01:51.620 --> 01:52.998
Money's in the till.

01:53.023 --> 01:54.566
You're doing this as a favor?

01:54.979 --> 01:56.785
I'm repaying an old debt.

01:57.636 --> 01:59.994
Don't pay more than you collect, kid.

02:00.019 --> 02:01.772
Passing credit back and forth

02:01.797 --> 02:05.084
is a good way to get stuck
with somebody forever.

02:09.799 --> 02:12.103
♪ Just living on a Sunday morning... ♪

02:12.241 --> 02:13.259
LIZ: Papi is

02:13.284 --> 02:15.640
- finally asleep.
- (LAUGHS SOFTLY)

02:15.665 --> 02:19.223
Clutching his rosary but asleep.

02:19.603 --> 02:22.226
I can't believe we're all
under the same roof.

02:24.395 --> 02:25.897
We're a family again.

02:25.922 --> 02:28.232
Yeah. I've been thinking.

02:28.495 --> 02:31.319
I think you should
move into Max's place.

02:31.448 --> 02:33.991
You can, you can get it
ready for his return,

02:34.016 --> 02:36.228
and do the whole domestic bliss...
thing.

02:36.253 --> 02:39.405
I'm so sorry. Who are you and
what happened to "how could you

02:39.430 --> 02:42.599
forgive the bastion of
white male privilege?"

02:42.871 --> 02:44.623
♪ Here and now... ♪

02:44.811 --> 02:46.163
(GASPS)

02:46.188 --> 02:47.780
(WHISPERS): You want your own room.

02:47.805 --> 02:50.694
I need... I deserve my own room, Liz.

02:50.719 --> 02:52.304
Oh, and Max is getting
stronger in there,

02:52.329 --> 02:53.772
but it is still going to be months

02:53.797 --> 02:55.675
before we can actually
attempt this surgery.

02:55.700 --> 02:56.975
I should be here.

02:57.931 --> 02:59.515
What if your dreams come back?

03:00.934 --> 03:03.358
I have not had any
freaky dreams in weeks.

03:03.383 --> 03:05.890
Okay, Max is probably
off haunting Isobel,

03:05.915 --> 03:08.140
now that they're strong
enough for their...

03:08.514 --> 03:12.518
psychic twincest weirdness.

03:13.222 --> 03:15.007
(STATIC CRACKLING)

03:18.430 --> 03:19.951
How long has that been happening?

03:20.145 --> 03:22.958
Um, I don't know. It's an old boom box.

03:24.510 --> 03:25.809
Rosa,

03:26.632 --> 03:30.536
have electrical appliances been
malfunctioning around you?

03:30.561 --> 03:34.536
I really thought it was just a
side effect of the handprint.

03:35.052 --> 03:36.378
If-if being in the pod

03:36.403 --> 03:38.778
introduced a new protein
into your system,

03:38.803 --> 03:40.309
it could have altered your DNA, too.

03:40.334 --> 03:42.497
You could be developing abilities.

03:42.522 --> 03:43.898
Liz.

03:44.588 --> 03:47.145
Look, the handprint is changing.
It's smaller.

03:47.953 --> 03:49.474
It's fading.

03:49.975 --> 03:51.950
Tell me this is a good thing.

03:54.793 --> 03:56.247
I don't think so.

03:56.731 --> 03:59.384
MICHAEL: The pod's got a charge.
It's like a, it's like a battery,

03:59.433 --> 04:01.138
powering the preservation process.

04:01.322 --> 04:02.536
This one's gone dead.

04:02.561 --> 04:04.817
Did the generator blow the
electromagnetic threshold?

04:04.842 --> 04:06.653
I think a surge came
from the pod itself.

04:06.678 --> 04:08.542
But that pod has lasted
almost a century.

04:08.567 --> 04:10.604
- It shouldn't glitch out.
- Okay, well, then, this one did.

04:10.629 --> 04:11.919
All right, stop.

04:12.402 --> 04:15.333
It doesn't matter why the pod is broken.
It just is.

04:15.358 --> 04:17.543
- So how long does Max have?
- My theory is

04:17.569 --> 04:19.177
that being tethered to
Rosa through the mark

04:19.202 --> 04:20.629
is what kept Max from going brain-dead,

04:20.654 --> 04:21.863
and in turn the stasis process

04:21.889 --> 04:23.434
is what kept the mark from fading.

04:23.459 --> 04:24.630
So he could be gone by tonight.

04:24.655 --> 04:26.282
Okay, well, we have three more pods.

04:26.536 --> 04:28.180
so let's just put him into another pod.

04:28.205 --> 04:29.552
ROSA: No.

04:29.974 --> 04:32.148
He's just gonna do it again.

04:32.891 --> 04:34.271
I haven't told you everything.

04:34.296 --> 04:35.943
I didn't want to scare
you, I didn't want

04:35.968 --> 04:37.427
to be the one that took the hope away.

04:37.452 --> 04:40.031
Talk now, Rosa. Right now.

04:40.411 --> 04:42.126
I was seeing Max in my nightmares

04:42.151 --> 04:44.607
months before I told you
about it, and he was

04:44.632 --> 04:46.060
begging me to stop you.

04:46.085 --> 04:48.205
He said that he was in a
lot of pain in there.

04:48.877 --> 04:51.529
That's Noah's pod. Noah
told us it was broken.

04:51.554 --> 04:54.380
It wasn't keeping him in stasis,
he could feel time passing.

04:54.405 --> 04:55.899
None of us thought of that.

04:56.032 --> 04:59.300
We've been doing everything
we can to make Max stronger.

05:01.630 --> 05:03.679
He pulled his own plug.

05:17.960 --> 05:19.946
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

05:22.878 --> 05:24.366
You've been avoiding me.

05:24.534 --> 05:26.193
Well, I learned you and
all of our friends

05:26.218 --> 05:28.066
have been lying to me
about aliens and murders

05:28.091 --> 05:29.224
and resurrection, so,

05:29.249 --> 05:31.334
haven't been feeling
particularly social.

05:33.741 --> 05:36.409
That being said, I fell for your ex,

05:36.494 --> 05:39.802
so I've decided, even though

05:39.827 --> 05:43.841
I'm still not speaking to
them, you and I are even?

05:43.973 --> 05:45.262
That's fair.

05:46.152 --> 05:47.945
(LAUGHS SOFTLY)

05:48.125 --> 05:49.433
What's up?

05:50.431 --> 05:52.007
Can't remember the password.

05:52.043 --> 05:55.316
And you want me to use my NSA
intelligence cryptology training

05:55.341 --> 05:57.051
to hack into your laptop?

05:58.327 --> 05:59.870
(CHUCKLES)

06:00.959 --> 06:02.732
How does any straight man survive you?

06:02.757 --> 06:05.032
(LAUGHS) They don't.

06:08.205 --> 06:10.041
How did you get here so fast?

06:10.080 --> 06:13.540
You called, I broke the speed limit.
What else is new?

06:13.577 --> 06:15.029
You ran a scan on Noah's heart?

06:15.054 --> 06:17.497
It's still too weak to transplant.

06:17.548 --> 06:20.923
We can't do anything to save
Max for at least eight weeks.

06:21.435 --> 06:23.384
Right. I knew that. Of course.

06:25.058 --> 06:27.137
Do you think it's true
that he's been in pain?

06:27.349 --> 06:29.473
Rosa's story keeps changing. I...

06:30.662 --> 06:33.153
I wrote a paper for a
bioethics class on patients

06:33.178 --> 06:34.645
in vegetative states who feel pain.

06:34.670 --> 06:36.005
Sometimes it's all they feel.

06:36.030 --> 06:39.154
That can't be it. Our experiment
was working. This is not over.

06:39.179 --> 06:41.403
No, you didn't fail. I mean, that heart

06:41.428 --> 06:43.374
was beyond repair, and now it's healing.

06:43.436 --> 06:46.314
In a few months, i-it'll be
viable again. That's insane.

06:46.423 --> 06:48.700
You are the smartest person I know,

06:49.535 --> 06:51.927
but your genius pales
compared to your compassion.

06:51.952 --> 06:53.536
And that's what we're up against now.

06:53.561 --> 06:55.792
We can't outsmart our own humanity.

06:55.817 --> 06:57.559
Okay, so what am I supposed to?

06:57.893 --> 07:00.145
Sit around and wait
for him to fade away?

07:00.880 --> 07:03.888
I think you're supposed to
use this time to find a way

07:03.913 --> 07:06.177
to say goodbye that gives you

07:06.959 --> 07:08.971
the best chance at living through it.

07:19.815 --> 07:21.526
Decision's gonna fall on you.

07:21.606 --> 07:24.300
I know, it's not fair.

07:24.401 --> 07:26.042
But Max is your person.

07:26.644 --> 07:28.128
(WHISPERS): Wow.

07:30.285 --> 07:31.828
There it is.

07:32.484 --> 07:34.235
- There what is?
- (CHUCKLES)

07:34.456 --> 07:36.503
You know, our whole lives,
you've kept your distance.

07:36.528 --> 07:38.924
And you've always insisted
that you're an outsider.

07:39.097 --> 07:40.245
And I never got that,

07:40.270 --> 07:42.463
because for me and Max, you were family.

07:42.576 --> 07:44.007
You always were.

07:44.290 --> 07:47.093
On the worst day, you
get to say, "Nope, no,

07:47.379 --> 07:48.887
he's your person,"

07:50.596 --> 07:53.140
pretend like he hasn't
been ours all along.

07:54.641 --> 07:55.917
I see that now.

07:55.942 --> 07:57.562
You got me.

07:59.075 --> 08:03.016
My abandonment issues
have all been a long con

08:03.041 --> 08:05.252
in case your half-resurrected brother

08:05.277 --> 08:09.656
decides to short-circuit his stasis pod.

08:13.691 --> 08:15.497
What are we gonna do, Isobel?

08:20.918 --> 08:22.377
I was pregnant

08:22.857 --> 08:24.206
when Noah died.

08:24.289 --> 08:28.752
I had, um, I had a touch choice to make.

08:28.846 --> 08:33.100
And I did it by imagining
that Max was there.

08:33.287 --> 08:37.058
Not just the platitudes and...
but the really tough questions.

08:37.871 --> 08:39.561
I'd have been there.

08:41.392 --> 08:42.981
I know.

08:45.380 --> 08:49.447
But it was a decision that
I had to make on my own.

08:49.650 --> 08:51.491
I mean, it was, it was terrifying,

08:51.549 --> 08:56.578
but I knew what was right for me.

08:57.952 --> 09:02.081
So I think you're wrong
about this decision.

09:02.167 --> 09:04.795
What happens to Max is not my choice.

09:05.446 --> 09:06.780
It's not yours.

09:06.936 --> 09:09.073
It doesn't matter how much we love him.

09:09.237 --> 09:10.448
If Rosa's right,

09:10.473 --> 09:13.596
then Max has already
made his own decision,

09:15.808 --> 09:17.518
to end his suffering.

09:22.117 --> 09:23.535
(SNIFFLES)

09:23.692 --> 09:25.449
Max is gonna die today.

09:25.474 --> 09:26.792
Yeah.

09:31.943 --> 09:33.828
I think he is.

09:37.862 --> 09:40.072
♪ ♪

09:40.962 --> 09:45.181
- Synced and corrected by martythecrazy -
- www.addic7ed.com -

09:56.645 --> 09:58.196
Is the handprint still there?

09:58.338 --> 10:01.766
It's smaller, but, yeah,
it's, it's still there.

10:03.174 --> 10:05.431
L-Liz, I'm really, really
sorry that I never told you

10:05.456 --> 10:07.691
what Max was asking me to do. I...

10:08.632 --> 10:13.259
I dreamed about you all
the time after you died.

10:13.551 --> 10:16.970
It hurt at first, waking up and
remembering you were still gone.

10:16.995 --> 10:21.813
But then, eventually, I started
to hope I'd dream of you.

10:23.392 --> 10:25.501
They felt like little visits.

10:29.150 --> 10:30.882
I never dream of Max.

10:31.788 --> 10:33.993
I mean, he can reach out to you,

10:34.018 --> 10:36.554
he can feel Isobel, I
don't even get a dream.

10:37.587 --> 10:39.009
You really wouldn't want to see him

10:39.034 --> 10:41.120
messed up the way he
is in my nightmares.

10:41.423 --> 10:43.220
It was that bad?

10:45.513 --> 10:47.712
Did he ever talk about me?

10:47.737 --> 10:49.817
He loved you so much.

10:51.300 --> 10:55.113
Are you kidding? I'm here
because he loved you.

10:59.118 --> 11:00.953
I don't know how I'm gonna live

11:01.201 --> 11:03.623
with letting him go.

11:05.551 --> 11:08.168
I never even told him I love him, too.

11:09.145 --> 11:10.921
How come you're not mad at me?

11:11.530 --> 11:13.007
For Michael?

11:13.539 --> 11:14.957
(SIGHS)

11:15.081 --> 11:16.954
The mess between us will
never be your fault.

11:16.979 --> 11:18.853
And plus, you didn't
know my history with him

11:18.878 --> 11:19.977
until after you hooked up.

11:20.002 --> 11:21.491
That's my fault. I should have told you.

11:21.516 --> 11:23.274
No, when I found out, I
should have stopped.

11:23.299 --> 11:26.555
Yeah, okay, you should
have, but you couldn't.

11:27.917 --> 11:30.274
How could I be mad at you for
falling for Michael Guerin?

11:31.043 --> 11:32.590
It's the easiest thing in the world.

11:32.641 --> 11:35.977
(SCOFFS) Yeah, until it's not.

11:36.321 --> 11:37.949
Don't write him off yet, okay?

11:37.979 --> 11:40.815
He keeps secrets because of how
much he loves Max and Isobel,

11:40.840 --> 11:42.953
not because of how much he loves you.

11:46.740 --> 11:49.531
You told me once that you
would stay in Roswell forever

11:49.556 --> 11:50.953
if the guy from the museum would just

11:50.978 --> 11:52.730
keep kissing you, but you did leave.

11:53.094 --> 11:54.631
What happened?

11:55.382 --> 11:58.164
That summer, Guerin
stopped being that guy.

11:58.234 --> 12:02.029
♪ Well, this heart of mine ♪

12:02.146 --> 12:05.766
♪ Has been hardened like a stone... ♪

12:06.093 --> 12:07.428
Ah!

12:07.453 --> 12:09.086
(GROANS) I'm so sorry.

12:09.111 --> 12:11.055
I'm so sorry. It's okay, I'm fine.

12:11.338 --> 12:12.915
- I'm fine.
- That is not healing right.

12:12.940 --> 12:14.652
You need to get it looked at.

12:15.504 --> 12:17.047
I'm fine.

12:17.072 --> 12:18.905
I just forgot about it for a second.

12:19.558 --> 12:21.450
Because for a second

12:22.130 --> 12:26.373
I forgot about everything except you.

12:26.469 --> 12:28.258
(CHUCKLES)

12:29.585 --> 12:32.837
♪ Well, I heard the news... ♪

12:34.048 --> 12:36.007
I can't be your medicine.

12:36.050 --> 12:37.176
What?

12:37.244 --> 12:41.290
You've changed since my
dad found us that night.

12:41.315 --> 12:42.780
You're starting fights with jocks.

12:42.805 --> 12:44.844
I know that you broke into
the drugstore last week.

12:44.869 --> 12:46.413
Now you're not going to UNM?

12:46.440 --> 12:47.695
That's a money thing.

12:47.720 --> 12:49.563
You got a scholarship.

12:51.390 --> 12:52.969
Look, I like doing this with you,

12:52.994 --> 12:55.578
but not if it's just so that you
can forget about something else,

12:55.603 --> 12:58.612
like how you and Max haven't
hung out at all this summer.

13:00.020 --> 13:01.438
Are you in love with Max?

13:01.463 --> 13:03.200
- Are you serious?
- Hey.

13:03.608 --> 13:05.469
You can tell me, okay?

13:05.494 --> 13:08.086
You guys were close, like, really close.

13:08.111 --> 13:11.524
Not like that. It's more than that,

13:11.549 --> 13:14.760
and it's-it's, it's less than that.

13:14.785 --> 13:17.274
We were friends when
we were kids, but now

13:17.675 --> 13:20.032
Max reminds me of a bunch of
stuff that I'd rather forget.

13:20.077 --> 13:24.555
The only thing that we have
in common anymore is Isobel.

13:24.915 --> 13:27.057
And before you ask,

13:27.421 --> 13:32.070
yeah... I'm totally in love with Isobel.

13:32.166 --> 13:34.043
(CHUCKLES)

13:35.606 --> 13:37.359
I want to be with you,

13:38.538 --> 13:40.248
but not if you're wasting your life.

13:40.273 --> 13:41.571
You know?

13:41.776 --> 13:44.492
♪ Well, baby, love don't live here. ♪

13:44.714 --> 13:48.579
(CLEARS THROAT) I begged
him to get it together,

13:48.689 --> 13:52.916
then he got busted for stealing
hubcaps, something like that.

13:53.115 --> 13:54.575
He was pushing you away.

13:54.654 --> 13:58.449
He does that. He hurts people
to see if they let him go.

13:58.667 --> 14:00.591
Made out with Lindsey
right in front of me.

14:00.650 --> 14:02.759
Yeah, well, I didn't need much pushing.

14:04.230 --> 14:06.721
He had become this walking bar fight,

14:06.762 --> 14:09.014
and I just could not deal.

14:09.302 --> 14:13.478
Hey. You grew up in an abusive home.

14:13.735 --> 14:15.565
It makes sense that you didn't want

14:15.590 --> 14:17.091
to be around all that anger.

14:17.212 --> 14:20.734
Yeah, and then the irony of
enlisting to escape violence.

14:21.235 --> 14:23.781
He was locked up the day that I left.

14:24.947 --> 14:26.783
I didn't get to say goodbye.

14:34.617 --> 14:36.076
Last year,

14:36.162 --> 14:40.046
a bullet tore my heart open,
and you put it back together.

14:40.174 --> 14:44.063
So... when your heart needed repair,

14:44.088 --> 14:46.508
I believed I could fix it, too.

14:54.279 --> 14:57.063
(SIGHS) I can't...

14:57.173 --> 14:58.883
No, no.

15:09.729 --> 15:11.537
(DOOR OPENS)

15:15.866 --> 15:17.584
(LAUGHING): Oh, my God.

15:17.910 --> 15:19.377
Biology club.

15:19.430 --> 15:21.307
Max hated science.

15:21.369 --> 15:22.870
He was in that club for four years

15:22.963 --> 15:25.766
just to watch your sister chew
on the end of her pencil.

15:26.235 --> 15:27.898
I was just grabbing
the last of my stuff.

15:27.923 --> 15:30.556
I'm gonna head out soon.
No, no, I'm here for you.

15:31.084 --> 15:33.225
- I need to talk to Max.
- What?

15:33.250 --> 15:35.743
I need to make sure that
it's him in your dreams,

15:35.768 --> 15:38.868
and not just some freaky
drug addict nightmare

15:38.893 --> 15:40.766
that you're having, no offense.

15:40.791 --> 15:42.704
Okay, you know you can't
just say "no offense"

15:42.729 --> 15:44.189
after you say something offensive.

15:44.217 --> 15:45.595
Okay.

15:45.620 --> 15:48.247
Right now there's no time for
my stunning personality.

15:48.280 --> 15:49.767
That handprint on your chest

15:49.792 --> 15:51.960
gives you direct access
to Max's brain waves.

15:51.985 --> 15:53.922
I need to use that channel
to get through to him,

15:53.947 --> 15:55.726
so if I mind-meld you, and then

15:55.751 --> 15:58.542
you find Max, the three of
us can have a three-way.

15:58.799 --> 16:00.126
Conference call.

16:01.126 --> 16:03.259
Look, I only see him

16:03.284 --> 16:04.452
when I'm asleep.

16:04.610 --> 16:07.009
Like I said, no time.

16:07.883 --> 16:10.471
Ooh, I'll beg forgiveness later.

16:15.423 --> 16:17.925
(HIGH-PITCHED RINGING)

16:23.649 --> 16:26.368
- You hit me with a thesaurus?
- (THUNDER RUMBLING)

16:26.393 --> 16:28.181
- Easy, girl.
- I know how to choke a bitch.

16:28.206 --> 16:30.337
- Stop it.
- Quit it.

16:30.575 --> 16:32.577
Isobel!

16:34.805 --> 16:37.080
Do all of your nightmares
look like this?

16:43.655 --> 16:47.757
I mean, they were all
creepy and dark, but...

16:49.467 --> 16:51.052
...not like this.

16:52.626 --> 16:54.223
Not broken.

16:57.037 --> 16:59.039
Max!

16:59.125 --> 17:00.329
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

17:00.438 --> 17:02.272
Max!

17:02.563 --> 17:05.192
(DISTORTED MUSIC PLAYING)

17:05.983 --> 17:08.468
I think the music is
coming from that way.

17:08.642 --> 17:10.195
Come on.

17:12.151 --> 17:16.202
(ENGINE NOT TURNING OVER)

17:16.759 --> 17:19.051
(SIGHS) Come on.

17:19.832 --> 17:21.747
♪ ♪

17:22.608 --> 17:24.126
We shouldn't come here anymore.

17:24.151 --> 17:25.818
I want to check on Mr. Ortecho.

17:25.843 --> 17:27.837
In case something bad happens to him?

17:31.522 --> 17:33.857
I think we should tell Isobel I did it.

17:34.084 --> 17:36.116
It's not fair that she
thinks it was you.

17:36.141 --> 17:37.464
She'd never believe you.

17:37.489 --> 17:39.699
If you take credit for a triple murder,

17:39.746 --> 17:42.122
the person who knows you
best is gonna ask questions.

17:42.147 --> 17:43.252
I'm the hothead,

17:43.277 --> 17:45.445
you are the hero. It's
always been that way.

17:45.641 --> 17:46.984
Just embrace it.

17:47.025 --> 17:49.361
Yeah, well, someone has
to clean up your messes.

17:49.819 --> 17:53.313
You stole the hubcaps off Kyle
Valenti's graduation present.

17:53.338 --> 17:55.950
Both his parents are cops.

17:56.487 --> 17:58.197
Do you want to end up in jail tonight?

17:58.222 --> 18:00.081
- Is that it?
- Where'd you get the bail money?

18:00.183 --> 18:03.103
Huh? Tutoring?

18:03.298 --> 18:05.560
- (MOCKING LAUGH)
- I'm gonna pay you back Friday.

18:05.585 --> 18:08.388
I got a gig lined up at
Foster ranch for the summer.

18:08.413 --> 18:10.340
Yeah, I know.

18:10.548 --> 18:12.050
How?

18:13.290 --> 18:16.752
Dad said they were hiring.
I didn't want the job, but

18:16.982 --> 18:18.932
I know you love the place.

18:20.426 --> 18:22.345
I didn't ask for that, Max.

18:23.757 --> 18:25.647
I never asked for you.

18:32.412 --> 18:35.795
(SCREAMING)

18:36.113 --> 18:37.909
Michael! Hey!

18:38.081 --> 18:40.037
- You okay?
- No!

18:40.075 --> 18:41.746
I can't commiserate with you right now.

18:41.771 --> 18:44.396
- I don't want to sit around and-and...
- Feeling feelings?

18:44.421 --> 18:46.428
Yeah, me neither, okay?

18:46.757 --> 18:50.046
We're doing the transplant tonight.

18:51.248 --> 18:53.467
Noah's heart might only keep
Max alive a few minutes.

18:53.492 --> 18:55.099
You're gonna put him
through surgery for that?

18:55.124 --> 18:57.751
He can either fade away in a
cave, trapped in his own hell,

18:57.776 --> 19:01.016
or he can spend his last moments
knowing how loved he was.

19:01.380 --> 19:05.224
You and Valenti, you
need me for the surgery?

19:05.252 --> 19:08.941
No, but you should be
there when he wakes up.

19:11.414 --> 19:14.488
Pretty sure Max has heard enough
out of me for one lifetime.

19:16.107 --> 19:18.234
When I got back to town, I asked Max

19:18.259 --> 19:21.764
why you and your brilliant mind
hadn't changed the world yet.

19:21.998 --> 19:23.914
He said you didn't care
about the world enough

19:23.939 --> 19:25.649
to bother changing it.

19:27.889 --> 19:29.920
He believed you could.

19:32.144 --> 19:34.675
Good luck getting his
car up and running.

19:39.010 --> 19:42.180
(DISTORTED MUSIC PLAYING)

19:44.615 --> 19:46.520
Hello?

19:47.311 --> 19:48.986
ROSA: This is the Crashdown,

19:49.011 --> 19:51.066
at least what's left of it in his mind.

19:54.656 --> 19:56.405
(MUSIC STOPS)

19:57.920 --> 19:59.991
Max!

20:00.459 --> 20:01.960
You're okay.

20:02.357 --> 20:05.022
I could feel something was wrong
with you. Everything felt...

20:05.047 --> 20:07.415
Cold. I know.

20:07.548 --> 20:09.210
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

20:09.659 --> 20:11.186
You can't be here.

20:11.240 --> 20:14.047
It's finally ending. I-I can feel it.

20:14.733 --> 20:16.282
But I don't know what-what happens

20:16.307 --> 20:18.084
if you're in my head when I die.

20:18.109 --> 20:19.701
So it's true?

20:21.405 --> 20:22.712
You want this?

20:22.737 --> 20:24.178
I could feel my connection

20:24.203 --> 20:26.046
to the outside world getting stronger,

20:26.071 --> 20:27.530
so I-I snapped.

20:27.555 --> 20:30.521
I couldn't take it anymore.
I released a surge.

20:31.499 --> 20:34.443
You have to let me go, Iz.

20:37.226 --> 20:38.614
Are you in?

20:38.850 --> 20:40.659
Did I just commit a felony?

20:41.406 --> 20:43.576
It's my mom's computer.

20:43.780 --> 20:46.538
Her nurse said that for the two
weeks before she went missing,

20:46.578 --> 20:48.456
when she wasn't trying to escape,

20:48.481 --> 20:50.615
she was talking to someone online.

20:50.640 --> 20:52.053
They let her have Internet?

20:52.244 --> 20:54.160
Well, she's a patient, not an inmate.

20:54.185 --> 20:56.126
She uses her computer to
watch Netflix and stuff.

20:56.151 --> 20:58.967
I don't know. I just want to
see this browser history.

21:00.289 --> 21:01.944
Somebody cleared her search history.

21:01.969 --> 21:04.555
- Excuse me.
- (BOTH CHUCKLE)

21:04.787 --> 21:06.608
No. You... It's okay.

21:06.633 --> 21:08.491
My mom was the last one
to use this computer.

21:08.516 --> 21:10.645
If she deleted it, she obviously

21:10.670 --> 21:12.701
didn't want anyone to know
what she was doing online.

21:12.726 --> 21:14.903
You know that if somebody
clears their search history,

21:14.928 --> 21:16.436
they are hiding something.

21:16.483 --> 21:18.257
I thought she wasn't
telling me her password

21:18.282 --> 21:19.777
because she couldn't remember it.

21:19.802 --> 21:22.282
If she didn't want me to
see something, then, hey.

21:22.657 --> 21:24.075
All the more reason to see it.

21:24.100 --> 21:25.545
I'm not investigating my mom.

21:25.570 --> 21:27.345
I just want to know who
might have taken her,

21:27.370 --> 21:29.092
but she's a victim.

21:30.133 --> 21:32.385
I'm not gonna invade
her privacy over it.

21:32.783 --> 21:34.327
She has a right to her secrets.

21:34.352 --> 21:35.712
(PHONE BUZZES)

21:35.748 --> 21:37.319
_

21:37.358 --> 21:39.982
_

21:40.007 --> 21:42.928
It's Valenti. I got to go.

21:43.153 --> 21:47.053
I like Kyle, but he was
terrible to you for so long.

21:47.305 --> 21:48.858
How have you forgiven him?

21:48.883 --> 21:50.718
Kyle and I aren't friends.

21:50.782 --> 21:53.062
I'm doing this because
it's my responsibility.

21:53.165 --> 21:54.475
I'm doing this for Liz.

21:54.543 --> 21:56.764
You know, something I learned
in the last ten years is,

21:56.789 --> 21:59.374
sometimes showing up is
the most important thing.

22:00.566 --> 22:02.364
Can't stay mad forever.

22:03.041 --> 22:04.918
People have a right to their secrets.

22:04.988 --> 22:06.659
(SCOFFS)

22:08.271 --> 22:10.164
I can't take it anymore.

22:10.198 --> 22:11.700
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

22:11.771 --> 22:13.397
Okay.

22:15.017 --> 22:16.268
I am so sorry.

22:16.293 --> 22:18.504
(SHUSHES)

22:19.634 --> 22:21.591
I just want to memorize this.

22:21.616 --> 22:24.345
(WHISPERS): Okay. Okay.

22:24.370 --> 22:26.998
I need you to tell Liz something.

22:27.023 --> 22:28.845
You can tell her yourself.

22:30.605 --> 22:32.356
She and Kyle are prepping for surgery.

22:32.381 --> 22:33.825
They're gonna use the faulty heart.

22:33.850 --> 22:35.615
She just wants to talk
to you before you die.

22:35.640 --> 22:37.405
- No. No.
- You won't be suffering.

22:37.430 --> 22:39.145
They're just gonna bring you
back and then let you go.

22:39.170 --> 22:40.670
No. You have to stop this.

22:40.695 --> 22:42.959
You cannot bring me back
under any circumstances.

22:42.984 --> 22:44.178
Max?

22:46.473 --> 22:48.058
What is really going on?

22:48.300 --> 22:50.119
I am dangerous.

22:51.213 --> 22:54.115
Whatever Liz is bringing back is not me.

22:54.309 --> 22:56.797
It's just some broken shell.

23:05.568 --> 23:08.505
(CRANKING WRENCH)

23:12.485 --> 23:14.102
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

23:14.742 --> 23:17.028
I'm not doing the 21st
birthday thing, Isobel.

23:17.053 --> 23:18.460
I don't do mechanical bulls

23:18.485 --> 23:20.608
and I don't do Garth Brooks karaoke.

23:21.062 --> 23:22.588
Well, that's a shame,

23:22.613 --> 23:26.073
because I came looking for my
friend in the lowest of places.

23:26.966 --> 23:28.825
I need help moving a body.

23:30.357 --> 23:31.692
Tequila?

23:31.786 --> 23:33.329
Yeah. Tequila.

23:33.837 --> 23:36.374
See, this is what happens
when you don't show up.

23:36.399 --> 23:38.131
Happy 21st birthday. Very mature.

23:38.156 --> 23:40.128
Somehow it's-it's my fault?

23:40.153 --> 23:41.490
Of course this is my fault.

23:41.547 --> 23:43.797
You know, you didn't just
stand Max up tonight.

23:43.822 --> 23:45.500
It's my birthday, too.

23:45.688 --> 23:49.180
Well, I'm sorry. I was very busy
with all of my underachieving.

23:49.301 --> 23:50.471
Hey.

23:50.496 --> 23:51.687
Hey, you made it.

23:51.758 --> 23:54.045
It's after midnight, and I had
to tempt him with a felony

23:54.070 --> 23:55.273
to get him out of his trailer.

23:55.298 --> 23:56.632
It doesn't count.

23:56.657 --> 23:58.015
(SLURRING): The thing is,

23:58.040 --> 24:00.070
there has to be three.

24:00.695 --> 24:03.751
Okay? There's always three.

24:03.776 --> 24:07.094
Until the very end. I'll show you.

24:07.119 --> 24:08.829
- I'll-I'll sh...
- This is crazy.

24:08.854 --> 24:11.022
I got this, right...

24:11.047 --> 24:12.424
MICHAEL: What's it mean?

24:12.449 --> 24:13.844
What it means...

24:13.869 --> 24:15.758
It means that you should be here.

24:16.146 --> 24:17.690
- You know?
- Mm-hmm.

24:17.715 --> 24:21.228
'Cause it's all broken without three.

24:22.241 --> 24:24.150
So we'll figure it out.

24:24.175 --> 24:25.802
You'll find your way back.

24:25.975 --> 24:27.603
I'm good, thanks.

24:27.767 --> 24:30.205
But I'll see you next time you
bring me in for petty larceny.

24:30.230 --> 24:31.439
(LAUGHS)

24:31.464 --> 24:33.509
- (LAUGHS)
- I-I will.

24:33.534 --> 24:36.581
Oh! Good night, Deputy.

24:36.606 --> 24:38.468
You know he did the whole
police academy thing

24:38.493 --> 24:39.573
because of you, right?

24:39.598 --> 24:40.909
He thinks you're gonna get
into the kind of trouble

24:40.934 --> 24:43.081
you can't get out of if
you don't know someone.

24:43.222 --> 24:45.768
I can pick locks with my brain.

24:45.793 --> 24:47.235
I don't need him.

24:47.260 --> 24:48.651
Yeah, I think he got that.

24:48.703 --> 24:51.643
(ENGINE STARTS)

24:53.667 --> 24:54.971
(THUMPING)

24:55.094 --> 24:57.049
Purring like a kitten.

24:57.074 --> 24:58.409
You don't do bad work

24:58.434 --> 25:00.394
once you pull your
finger out of your nose.

25:00.419 --> 25:03.284
Yeah, we both know I do the
best work in the state.

25:04.323 --> 25:06.534
Regardless of where my fingers are.

25:07.721 --> 25:09.139
What was it?

25:09.980 --> 25:11.315
There was too much tension

25:11.340 --> 25:12.967
between the alternator and the battery.

25:12.992 --> 25:14.870
Had to reset the coils,
figure out a new way

25:14.903 --> 25:16.446
for them to talk to each other.

25:21.410 --> 25:23.096
I'm gonna need the rest of the day off.

25:24.376 --> 25:25.964
Uh... a family emergency.

25:25.989 --> 25:27.964
Yeah, well, I got a ice skating date

25:27.989 --> 25:29.846
in hell with the tooth fairy.

25:52.087 --> 25:54.307
I figured it all out.

25:54.371 --> 25:56.987
See, there's a-an energy to suffering,

25:57.012 --> 25:58.768
there's an energy to death.

25:58.793 --> 26:02.255
And when I heal people,
I absorb that energy.

26:02.280 --> 26:05.116
So, when I resurrected Rosa,

26:05.356 --> 26:09.096
I took in ten years of emptiness.

26:09.121 --> 26:13.448
So if you resurrect me, you will
be bringing back an infection.

26:13.473 --> 26:15.422
Don't want... I don't want
to come back as a monster.

26:15.447 --> 26:17.678
I don't want to hurt anyone

26:17.703 --> 26:19.370
that I care about.

26:19.866 --> 26:21.728
That's what this is about?

26:23.825 --> 26:25.868
We've been hurting, Max.

26:25.893 --> 26:28.072
- We don't work without you.
- You will!

26:28.097 --> 26:29.932
You will. You are stronger now

26:29.957 --> 26:31.064
than when I died.

26:31.089 --> 26:32.507
All of you are.

26:32.532 --> 26:36.017
You and Michael, Liz,
you will survive this.

26:36.042 --> 26:37.711
The three of you.

26:37.736 --> 26:39.738
No, you need to stop them, Iz.

26:39.763 --> 26:41.494
Now.

26:43.718 --> 26:45.261
Okay.

26:46.316 --> 26:47.859
I love you.

26:48.648 --> 26:50.291
You, too.

27:01.656 --> 27:03.351
I'm sorry this is happening.

27:03.437 --> 27:06.387
(GRUNTS) Isobel is lying.

27:06.412 --> 27:09.351
She is buying time. You know
she'll never let me go.

27:09.620 --> 27:11.705
But you can feel the darkness,
too, though, right?

27:11.744 --> 27:13.632
That's why you don't
like being in my head.

27:13.657 --> 27:15.898
Because you know it's real.

27:15.923 --> 27:17.937
I didn't want that to be true, but yes.

27:17.962 --> 27:19.990
I know my sister and I know your sister,

27:20.015 --> 27:21.101
and they'll never give up.

27:21.126 --> 27:24.062
So you have to be the one
to stop the surgery.

27:24.261 --> 27:28.304
Okay, or I will destroy
everything that we love.

27:29.525 --> 27:33.163
You have to stop them to save them.

27:33.452 --> 27:35.079
Now go.

27:35.227 --> 27:37.085
Please, Rosa, go.

27:39.307 --> 27:40.898
(COUGHS)

27:41.463 --> 27:42.992
(SIGHS)

27:44.489 --> 27:46.199
What?

27:48.318 --> 27:51.281
Hey! Hello?

27:53.206 --> 27:55.851
Oh, these bitch-ass aliens.

27:57.793 --> 27:59.881
He was begging you to let him die?

27:59.906 --> 28:02.648
Yeah. And not to relieve
his suffering, either,

28:02.673 --> 28:05.101
but because he's scared
he's going to hurt us.

28:05.421 --> 28:08.163
If-if Max survives at all,
he is going to be weak.

28:08.188 --> 28:11.874
When he saved Rosa, he absorbed
all of that dark energy.

28:11.899 --> 28:13.577
He's gonna have to expel it.

28:14.944 --> 28:18.148
And-and he's afraid he's gonna
kill someone when he does.

28:19.500 --> 28:21.015
Yeah.

28:25.440 --> 28:28.732
So we just need someone stronger
than Max to take that hit.

28:28.757 --> 28:29.804
Isobel...

28:29.829 --> 28:31.632
Look, if he thinks that
he needs to protect us,

28:31.657 --> 28:33.913
he obviously doesn't
know how capable we are.

28:35.154 --> 28:37.304
Bring him back, Liz.

28:39.771 --> 28:41.531
I'll handle the rest.

28:41.853 --> 28:45.773
("KEEP YOU SAFE" BY LINDSEY RAY PLAYING)

28:47.784 --> 28:49.546
Okay. Everything's secured.

28:50.187 --> 28:52.351
Hospital staff thinks
that a highly-classified

28:52.376 --> 28:53.843
VIP patient's being treated.

28:53.868 --> 28:56.007
- They won't bother you.
- And Michael?

28:56.519 --> 28:59.210
Uh, we've been calling.
There's no answer.

29:01.136 --> 29:02.734
Good luck.

29:05.822 --> 29:10.421
♪ Ooh... ♪

29:10.463 --> 29:13.633
♪ Ooh ♪

29:13.664 --> 29:18.437
♪ I will light the path for ♪

29:18.479 --> 29:23.179
♪ You... ♪

29:23.261 --> 29:26.296
♪ Ooh ♪

29:26.335 --> 29:27.878
♪ I'll do ♪

29:27.903 --> 29:30.890
♪ All that I can ♪

29:30.933 --> 29:34.452
♪ Do ♪

29:35.767 --> 29:39.242
♪ To keep you safe ♪

29:48.623 --> 29:53.077
♪ Ooh ♪

29:53.118 --> 29:55.671
(GRUNTS)

29:56.546 --> 30:01.539
♪ I will light the path for ♪

30:01.564 --> 30:06.327
♪ You... ♪

30:06.352 --> 30:09.147
♪ Ooh ♪

30:09.202 --> 30:14.202
♪ I'll do all that I can ♪

30:14.243 --> 30:19.007
♪ Do... ♪

30:19.116 --> 30:21.868
♪ Ooh... ♪

30:22.016 --> 30:24.249
You got this look in your eyes
like you think I'm crazy.

30:24.318 --> 30:26.792
This look? I get this look every time

30:26.817 --> 30:28.714
I use my workplace to
conduct an impossible

30:28.739 --> 30:31.536
emergency alien heart transplant, solo.

30:31.561 --> 30:33.239
He's gonna die, Liz.

30:33.278 --> 30:35.413
We're risking everything
to do this, and maybe...

30:35.438 --> 30:38.534
Maybe... he lives long enough for
you to get a minute with him

30:38.559 --> 30:39.692
before that heart gives out.

30:39.717 --> 30:40.950
A minute is all I need.

30:41.394 --> 30:46.512
♪ To... keep you safe. ♪

31:06.393 --> 31:08.403
You need a break? A water?

31:08.428 --> 31:09.629
You don't need to check on me.

31:09.654 --> 31:12.059
There's a reason surgeons
don't operate on loved ones.

31:12.184 --> 31:13.734
Holding someone's future in your hands

31:13.759 --> 31:14.856
when you're personally invested is...

31:14.881 --> 31:16.299
I'm okay, Kyle.

31:16.498 --> 31:18.661
And there is nothing that's
gonna happen here today

31:18.686 --> 31:21.497
that'll change how grateful I am to you.

31:22.043 --> 31:23.586
I will never be able to repay you

31:23.611 --> 31:26.036
- for everything that you've...
- You never have to.

31:27.133 --> 31:29.559
(SIGHS) We're family.

31:30.682 --> 31:32.869
♪ I see it in your eyes... ♪

31:32.894 --> 31:35.182
- (FOOTFALLS APPROACHING)
- (PANTING)

31:35.207 --> 31:36.572
Oh, my God.

31:37.662 --> 31:39.497
I didn't think you'd make it.

31:39.522 --> 31:41.483
No, I'm here.

31:41.927 --> 31:43.470
I get it now.

31:43.997 --> 31:45.499
It's got to be the three of us.

31:45.524 --> 31:46.692
What?

31:46.870 --> 31:48.447
Where's the operating room?

31:48.472 --> 31:52.752
♪ Never give up, don't give up now... ♪

31:53.063 --> 31:54.640
MICHAEL: It inserts subdermally.

31:54.665 --> 31:56.455
To monitor and nudge the pulse.

31:56.480 --> 31:58.232
It keeps it steady and strong.

31:58.257 --> 31:59.541
If it works,

31:59.566 --> 32:00.901
it'll buy us time.

32:01.103 --> 32:02.354
Years or longer.

32:02.379 --> 32:03.630
I thought you'd given up.

32:03.854 --> 32:06.322
Yeah. It's what I do.

32:06.347 --> 32:09.559
Thing is, Max... he doesn't.

32:09.824 --> 32:11.822
He would never pull his plug
to end his own suffering.

32:11.847 --> 32:13.828
Unless he thought he was
saving us from something.

32:13.853 --> 32:16.204
And I'm a little sick of
his heroic martyr crap.

32:16.229 --> 32:17.283
It's a pain in the ass.

32:17.308 --> 32:19.908
So you built an alien
pacemaker in seven hours.

32:20.053 --> 32:22.135
My genius increases when I'm pissed off.

32:22.160 --> 32:23.661
Thank you.

32:24.912 --> 32:28.260
♪ Never give up, don't give up now ♪

32:28.285 --> 32:31.413
♪ There's still hope
in the darkest hour ♪

32:31.438 --> 32:35.486
♪ Never give up, don't give up now ♪

32:37.464 --> 32:41.838
♪ I'll take this pain for you ♪

32:41.863 --> 32:44.772
♪ I will pull you through ♪

32:44.797 --> 32:49.588
- ♪ I'll be with you till the end ♪
- (MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY)

32:49.613 --> 32:51.283
♪ With you till the end... ♪

32:51.308 --> 32:52.885
We got it ticking.

32:52.910 --> 32:54.838
Now we just need to keep it going.

32:54.863 --> 32:57.157
♪ Through the fire and rain ♪

32:57.182 --> 32:59.059
All right, time to attach the pacemaker.

32:59.084 --> 33:01.072
♪ I will be your strength ♪

33:01.097 --> 33:04.994
♪ I'll be with you till the end ♪

33:05.019 --> 33:11.966
♪ With you till the end ♪

33:11.991 --> 33:18.541
♪ With you till the end... ♪

33:26.677 --> 33:28.119
(ALARM SOUNDING)

33:28.386 --> 33:30.002
He's crashing.

33:30.337 --> 33:32.174
Ready the defibrillators.

33:34.956 --> 33:37.378
♪ I'll be with you till the end... ♪

33:37.403 --> 33:38.659
Rosa, what are you doing?

33:38.684 --> 33:41.103
- I'm sorry, but he begged me.
- Wh-What?

33:41.128 --> 33:46.659
- (ALARM BLARING)
- (MONITOR FLATLINING)

33:48.097 --> 33:50.331
Charge. Clear!

33:50.356 --> 33:51.816
Shock!

33:52.858 --> 33:54.193
Still flatlining.

33:54.724 --> 33:56.011
No response at all.

33:56.036 --> 33:58.038
Damn it. More power.

33:58.063 --> 33:59.189
Charge.

34:00.151 --> 34:01.370
Clear.

34:01.395 --> 34:03.237
Shock.

34:04.357 --> 34:07.550
Still no response. Let's go again.

34:07.751 --> 34:09.206
Charge.

34:09.231 --> 34:10.478
Clear.

34:10.504 --> 34:12.112
Shock.

34:12.495 --> 34:14.167
Max!

34:14.411 --> 34:17.681
(BOTH GRUNTING)

34:19.117 --> 34:22.076
- You can't be here, Iz, you have to go.
- No. No, no, no.

34:22.101 --> 34:24.951
I'm not gonna let you go alone, okay?

34:24.976 --> 34:26.527
I'm never gonna let you go alone.

34:26.553 --> 34:30.983
♪ They're spreading
blankets on the beach... ♪

34:31.007 --> 34:32.498
(CRYING): No, no, no.

34:33.643 --> 34:36.648
♪ Yours was the first face that I saw ♪

34:36.858 --> 34:40.248
♪ I think I was blind
before I met you. ♪

34:40.433 --> 34:43.295
(MONITOR FLATLINING)

34:45.549 --> 34:47.300
There's not enough power.

34:47.800 --> 34:50.451
The defibrillator's cranked
up as high as it will go.

34:51.703 --> 34:54.576
It's not meant for a heart
that's been dead for months.

34:54.601 --> 34:56.130
(LIZ GASPS)

34:56.297 --> 34:58.490
No. No!

35:00.224 --> 35:03.396
(SOBBING)

35:12.086 --> 35:13.373
I have to call it.

35:13.398 --> 35:15.025
No.

35:23.428 --> 35:24.854
Do it again.

35:26.953 --> 35:28.386
Do it again!

35:28.419 --> 35:30.581
Come on, one more time. You have to.

35:33.308 --> 35:34.347
Charge.

35:34.380 --> 35:36.152
(POWER SURGES)

35:36.248 --> 35:37.620
Clear.

35:37.645 --> 35:40.180
Shock!

35:45.012 --> 35:49.231
(MONITOR BEEPS STEADILY)

35:51.660 --> 35:54.695
(MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY)

35:56.385 --> 35:59.531
Uh, I, uh... I just came
to check on the pacemaker.

35:59.556 --> 36:01.552
I'm gonna come back. No, no, no.
Hey, hey, hey.

36:01.577 --> 36:03.413
Stay. Stay.

36:08.022 --> 36:10.352
What were you gonna do if the
pacemaker hadn't worked?

36:10.377 --> 36:14.953
I... would've kept him comfortable

36:14.978 --> 36:16.313
for as long as possible.

36:16.387 --> 36:18.762
I would have told him I love him.

36:19.599 --> 36:22.921
And if his heart stopped beating

36:22.946 --> 36:25.143
and there was nothing I could do...

36:26.061 --> 36:27.730
I would've said goodbye.

36:28.872 --> 36:31.998
But we don't have to live in that

36:32.023 --> 36:33.900
"what if" scenario anymore.

36:33.925 --> 36:35.987
We saved him.

36:36.012 --> 36:37.805
We're gonna keep him in the coma

36:37.830 --> 36:39.418
until he's strong enough to wake up.

36:39.443 --> 36:42.284
And he will wake up.

36:43.557 --> 36:46.143
Whatever happens next,
we're gonna handle it.

36:46.168 --> 36:48.178
Max is alive, Michael.

37:07.468 --> 37:11.725
First thing I remember
is the three of us.

37:13.242 --> 37:15.610
We woke up terrified and lost

37:17.021 --> 37:18.398
but together.

37:18.863 --> 37:21.366
And then all of a sudden I was alone.

37:21.967 --> 37:24.326
And I got real good at being alone.

37:24.827 --> 37:27.120
I'd given up on people entirely.

37:27.145 --> 37:29.449
♪ Somewhere past tomorrow... ♪

37:29.488 --> 37:32.418
And then you found me again.

37:32.543 --> 37:35.255
♪ The life you live in dreams ♪

37:35.518 --> 37:37.340
Hell of a hero move.

37:37.982 --> 37:39.679
You showed up just in time.

37:39.704 --> 37:41.343
♪ If you're ever broken ♪

37:41.368 --> 37:44.298
♪ There's always an open door ♪

37:44.323 --> 37:46.723
♪ A beacon toward the shore ♪

37:46.887 --> 37:49.102
♪ Sometimes it takes dark... ♪

37:49.250 --> 37:51.187
When you are a kid who nobody loves,

37:51.212 --> 37:53.175
kindness is a currency.

37:53.200 --> 37:54.411
♪ Sometimes you need fire... ♪

37:54.436 --> 37:56.488
Friendship doesn't mean jack.

37:56.965 --> 38:00.028
Family just lies and hurts and leaves.

38:01.448 --> 38:04.032
I've only ever known
love to be temporary.

38:07.430 --> 38:11.111
♪ 'Cause the stars are on your side ♪

38:11.136 --> 38:13.458
So, yeah, I push people away.

38:14.035 --> 38:17.038
Every time someone threatens
to care about me,

38:17.094 --> 38:19.506
I test their love until
they have to leave.

38:20.312 --> 38:23.010
♪ ♪

38:25.253 --> 38:26.723
(TRUCK DOOR OPENS)

38:26.858 --> 38:28.557
(TRUCK DOOR SHUTS)

38:29.373 --> 38:31.419
♪ If you're holding breath... ♪

38:31.444 --> 38:33.353
Connection is conditional.

38:33.937 --> 38:36.732
Everybody eventually gives up on the guy

38:36.757 --> 38:38.817
who refuses to be rescued.

38:40.696 --> 38:43.155
♪ Know you're bound for glory ♪

38:43.285 --> 38:46.159
♪ And that all is never lost ♪

38:46.185 --> 38:47.795
♪ No matter the cost... ♪

38:47.820 --> 38:50.514
But y-you were the only one
that I could never run off.

38:50.650 --> 38:54.082
You never believed me when I
tried to be something I wasn't.

38:54.652 --> 38:57.085
♪ Sometimes you need fire ♪

38:57.244 --> 39:00.380
♪ To see you through the other side ♪

39:00.513 --> 39:03.141
♪ So get up off your knees ♪

39:03.235 --> 39:05.131
♪ Hope is still alive... ♪

39:05.255 --> 39:07.763
So, this thing in your chest...

39:08.908 --> 39:11.897
it might give your heart
a pretty solid kick

39:11.922 --> 39:13.248
every once in a while.

39:13.273 --> 39:15.562
Consider it payback.

39:16.282 --> 39:18.857
It's my hero move, Max.

39:20.193 --> 39:24.738
If you wake up, you
consider us even, okay?

39:25.578 --> 39:28.533
♪ ♪

39:31.244 --> 39:33.789
If you wake up, we can be a family.

39:36.333 --> 39:37.856
Where's Isobel?

39:39.342 --> 39:41.171
She's getting ready.

39:41.531 --> 39:44.674
Getting ready... for what?

39:47.702 --> 39:51.912
_

39:52.506 --> 39:54.893
(SHUDDERING)

40:01.668 --> 40:03.318
(GROANS)

40:04.583 --> 40:06.279
Welcome back.

40:07.024 --> 40:09.784
You've been in a medically
induced coma for 12 years.

40:09.809 --> 40:11.342
Taylor Swift is president now,

40:11.367 --> 40:13.663
which, honestly, is for the best.

40:14.232 --> 40:16.271
I begged you to understand.

40:16.296 --> 40:17.819
Max, it's gonna be fine.

40:17.844 --> 40:19.502
No.

40:32.275 --> 40:35.670
I told you to let me go.

40:35.695 --> 40:39.491
I can feel it inside me.

40:39.640 --> 40:41.683
It's, it's symmetry. Okay?

40:41.708 --> 40:44.818
It's just energy for energy.
We can deal with that.

40:46.146 --> 40:47.564
Fight it, Max.

40:47.589 --> 40:48.674
This isn't you.

40:48.699 --> 40:49.866
I don't want to hurt you.

40:49.891 --> 40:51.744
I need to get out.

40:51.769 --> 40:54.181
I need to get away from
you, from everyone.

40:54.206 --> 40:56.288
I can't let you do that.

40:57.491 --> 40:59.625
(GROANS)

41:09.072 --> 41:10.908
(GROANS)

41:11.377 --> 41:13.847
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

41:15.606 --> 41:18.393
(HIGH-PITCHED RINGING)

41:24.012 --> 41:26.181
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

41:28.425 --> 41:29.885
I made a promise

41:29.910 --> 41:32.827
that if you came back
and you weren't Max,

41:32.852 --> 41:35.160
and you were actually gonna hurt people,

41:35.891 --> 41:37.454
that I would kill you.

41:37.833 --> 41:39.482
I figure, hey,

41:39.507 --> 41:41.416
you got to play God.

41:41.441 --> 41:44.366
Make life and death
decisions all on your own.

41:44.391 --> 41:45.463
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

41:45.488 --> 41:47.507
Well, it's my turn now.

41:47.655 --> 41:49.295
(THUNDER CRACKS)

41:49.524 --> 41:52.131
We can be a matching set.

